Intro e filmes

Tal como vínhamos fazendo antes:

library(ggplot2movies)
glimpse(movies)

filmes = movies %>% 
    filter(year >= 1970, 
           length >= 90, length <= 180, 
           Action == 1, 
           budget > 1e5) %>% 
    mutate(age = (2017 - year), 
           title = paste0(title, " (", year, ")"), 
           love = r10/(r10 + r1)) %>%
    select(title, age, budget, love, votes) %>%
    filter(complete.cases(.)) # complete.cases recebe um df, e não vetores como entrada

Agrupando com kmeans

set.seed(123)
explorando_k = tibble(k = 1:15) %>% 
    group_by(k) %>% 
    do(
        kmeans(select(filmes_transformado, -title), 
               centers = .$k, 
               nstart = 20) %>% glance()
    )
explorando_k %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = k, y = tot.withinss)) + 
    geom_line() + 
    geom_point()

Github data

load_github_wide <- function(){
  d <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nazareno/ciencia-de-dados-1/master/3-Agrupamento-e-PCA/dados/atividade-no-github-archive-2012-2015.csv", stringsAsFactors = TRUE)
  
  # Somente o que queremos. E usaremos eventos/repo
  d$events <- d$events / d$active_repos_by_url
  d <- filter(d, year == 2014, quarter == 1, type != "CreateEvent") %>% 
    select(-active_repos_by_url, -year, -quarter)
  d$type <- droplevels(d$type)
  
  dw <- dcast(d, repository_language ~ type, value.var = "events")
  dw <- filter(dw, complete.cases(dw))
  return(dw)
}
dw <- load_github_wide()
Error in dcast(d, repository_language ~ type, value.var = "events") :

require(Rtsne)
iris2 = iris %>% 
    filter(!duplicated(iris)) %>% 
    mutate_at(vars(-Species), funs(scale)) 

tsne.out = Rtsne(select(iris2, -Species), 
                 verbose = FALSE, 
                 perplexity = 20) # as vezes é uma boa brincar com esse parâmetro

df = as.data.frame(tsne.out$Y)
df$Species = iris2$Species
